    {\displaystyle x_{i}|\theta \sim P(\theta )}
  , and if the prior is Gamma distributed 
  
    
      
        θ
        ∼
        G
        (
        a
        ,
        b
        )
      
    
    {\displaystyle \theta \sim G(a,b)}
  , then the posterior is also Gamma distributed, and the Bayes estimator under MSE is given by
  
    
      
        
          
            
