        −
        
          θ
          ′
        
        )
        d
        
          θ
          ′
        
        .
      
    
    {\displaystyle \int L(a-\theta )f(x_{1}-\theta )d\theta =\int L(a-x_{1}-\theta ')f(-\theta ')d\theta '.}
          (2)This is identical to (1), except that 
  
    
      
        a
      
    
    {\displaystyle a}
   has been replaced by 
  
    
      
        a
        −
        
          x
          
            1
          
        
      
    
    {\displaystyle a-x_{1}}
  . Thus, the expression minimizing is given by 
  
    
      
        a
        −
        
          x
          
            1
          
        
